The paper discusses the design metrics of asynchronous adders, which falls under the category of electronic design automation (EDA) and computer architecture. Therefore, cs.ET (EDA and VLSI Technology), cs.AR (Computer Architecture), and cs.DC (Digital Circuits) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a CMOS process, which is related to semiconductor technology, making cs.DS (Digital Systems) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses low power/energy design, which is a common concern in embedded systems, making cs.EM (Embedded Systems) a possible sub-category as well.
